# My Falt Leap Application

A web application built with Falt Leap Framework - a radically simple, zero-dependency PHP framework for PostgreSQL.

## Quick Start

### 1. Configure Database

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure your PostgreSQL connection:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env`:
```
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USERNAME=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=yourpassword
DB_DATABASE=myapp
DB_SCHEMA=public
```

### 2. Create Database Schema

Create your tables in PostgreSQL:

```sql
CREATE TABLE users (
    idusers SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    email VARCHAR(100),
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### 3. Generate Models

```bash
php vendor/bin/gen all public
```

This will generate Active Record models in the `models/` directory.

### 4. Define Routes

Edit `conf/router.config.php`:

```php
$routes = [
    "/" => "HomeController@index",
    "/users" => "UsersController@index",
    "/users/{id}" => "UsersController@show"
];
```

### 5. Create Controllers

Controllers go in the `app/` directory and extend `LeapController`:

```php
<?php
namespace App\Controllers;

use FlatLeap\LeapController;
use App\Models\Users;

class UsersController extends LeapController
{
    public function index()
    {
        $users = Users::Query()->get();
        $this->view->data = $users;
        $this->view->render('users/index');
    }
}
```

### 6. Create Views

Views go in the `views/` directory with `.leap.php` extension:

```php
<!-- views/users/index.leap.php -->
<h1>Users</h1>
<ul>
    <?php foreach ($data as $user): ?>
        <li><?= htmlspecialchars($user->username) ?></li>
    <?php endforeach; ?>
</ul>
```

### 7. Run Development Server

Using Docker:
```bash
./run.sh
```

Visit http://localhost:8090

## Project Structure

```
/app/               Controllers
/models/            Auto-generated models
/views/             Templates (.leap.php)
/public/            Web root
/conf/              Configuration
  router.config.php Routes
/storage/           Session storage
/middleware/        Custom middleware
.env                Environment config
```

